<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<FindBugsFilter xmlns="https://github.com/spotbugs/filter/3.0.0">
  <!--
    Reviewed suppressions (Chapter 16: suppress with a reason, never disable a whole detector).

    This module ships one deliberate counter-example whose defect IS the lesson: an AI-drafted lookup
    that concatenates an input into its SQL text, so a test can prove the vulnerability-inheritance the
    prose describes rather than merely assert it. The detectors are left fully ENABLED for the rest of
    the module (the reviewed PreparedStatement fix, the inventory code under test, and the AiReviewGate
    running path all stay clean); only the named counter-example core SpotBugs raises at this module's
    threshold carries a finding, suppressed narrowly, with a reason, and pointed at the test that
    demonstrates it. The finding was verified load-bearing (BugInstance size is 1 with this filter
    empty, 0 with it as below, deterministic across runs). Fixing the class — which ReviewedLookup
    already does — is the real advice; the suppression exists only so the teaching counter-example ships
    green.

    The chapter's thesis is exactly this firing: a SQL injection is caught by the same SpotBugs rule
    whether a human or a model wrote it. The gate does not care who wrote the code.
  -->

  <!--
    Injection (OWASP A03 / CWE-89), AI-drafted. AiDraftedLookup.findIdsByEmail builds its query by
    string concatenation and passes the nonconstant String to Statement.executeQuery, so SpotBugs
    raises SQL_NONCONSTANT_STRING_PASSED_TO_EXECUTE (verified to fire here, so the suppression is
    load-bearing, not decorative). The finding IS the vulnerability-inheritance lesson, so it is named
    as an intentional teaching counter-example. Proven by
    AiGeneratedCodeQualityTest.AiDraftGoesThroughTheGate#stringConcatenationFoldsTheInputIntoTheQueryText.
    The fix is the bound '?' parameter in ReviewedLookup.findIdsByEmail, never this suppression.
  -->
  <Match>
    <Class name="org.acme.ai.AiDraftedLookup"/>
    <Method name="findIdsByEmail"/>
    <Bug pattern="SQL_NONCONSTANT_STRING_PASSED_TO_EXECUTE"/>
  </Match>
</FindBugsFilter>
